                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.9415 Amur River/10: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-03T11:00:00+09:00"
                            >July 3, 1937—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 3—1:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>176. My 174, July 2, 2 p.m. A press dispatch from Moscow reports that Shigemitsu
                    announced on July 2 that the Soviet Government consented to withdraw its forces
                    from the occupied Amur River islands and to return to their stations the Soviet
                    gunboats concentrated in that vicinity.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
